<TITLE> Bay low puts ports on alert </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 23 (bdnews24.com)  The low over southwest Bay of Bengal and the adjoining area moved northwards and intensified into a well-marked low, a weather bulletin issued on Saturday said. The low was now lying over southwest Bay and adjoining west central Bay. Its associated trough extended to north Bay and was likely to intensify further, the Meteorological Department said. Under its influence deep convection was taking place over north Bay. The maritime ports of Chittagong, Cox's Bazar and Mongla have been told to hoist local cautionary signal number 3, the bulletin said. All fishing boats and trawlers over north Bay and deep sea were asked to stay close to the coast and proceed with caution until further not
